(HAPP SOLUTION DOCUMENTATION) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Project: Hardware-Agnostic Performance Profiler \(HAPP\)) Tj
T* (Audience: Lecturer presentation) Tj
T* (Repository: Hardware-Agnostic-Performance-Profiler-HAPP-) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (HAPP is a C++17 command-line simulator that estimates application performance under constrained) Tj
T* (hardware profiles. Instead of emulating CPU instructions, it applies a practical analytical) Tj
T* (model across compute, storage I/O, network throughput, and memory pressure so developers can) Tj
T* (compare scenarios quickly.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. PROBLEM CONTEXT) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Embedded and IoT software often fails when moved from high-performance development machines to) Tj
T* (lower-resource targets. Typical gaps include:) Tj
T* (• Underestimated memory needs) Tj
T* (• Hidden compute bottlenecks) Tj
T* (• Storage-induced slowdowns) Tj
T* (• Network sensitivity for transfer-heavy tasks) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (HAPP addresses these by simulating “what-if” hardware environments using configurable) Tj
T* (parameters \(CPU cores, RAM, storage class, network Mbps\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. PROJECT GOALS) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (• Provide a lightweight hardware-constrained performance estimation tool.) Tj
T* (• Make bottleneck causes explicit \(CPU, RAM, storage, network\).) Tj
T* (• Support repeatable CLI workflows for simulation, comparison, and config persistence.) Tj
T* (• Remain extensible for future telemetry and deeper resource modeling.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (4. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (HAPP is organized into focused modules:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (• CLI layer \(cli_parser, cli_runner\): command parsing, option validation, and user-facing) Tj
T* (reporting.) Tj
T* (• Hardware model \(hardware_config, storage_type\): machine profile representation and storage) Tj
T* (classification.) Tj
T* (• Workload model \(workload_spec\): task type, complexity, and size controls.) Tj
T* (• Simulation engine \(simulation_engine\): core estimation model for time and resource usage.) Tj
T* (• Profiler analysis \(bottleneck_analyzer\): bottleneck detection, warnings, and recommendations.) Tj
T* (• Result reporting \(simulation_result\): normalized output object and printable report.) Tj
T* (• Utilities \(config_file, virtual_memory\): config persistence and educational fixed-capacity) Tj
T* (allocator.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5. IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
