(• labels primary bottleneck \(RAM, CPU, Storage I/O, Network\),) Tj
T* (• emits warnings for risky conditions \(e.g., low RAM, HDD with I/O-heavy task\),) Tj
T* (• provides targeted recommendations.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Recommendations are deduplicated while preserving insertion order.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5.6 CONFIGURATION PERSISTENCE) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (load_happ_config and save_happ_config support key=value profiles. Config files can be layered) Tj
T* (via --config and overridden by later CLI flags.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (5.7 VIRTUAL MEMORY UTILITY) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (VirtualMemory demonstrates fixed-capacity allocation using a bump-pointer model. It currently) Tj
T* (serves as a simple educational mechanism and extension point for future memory pressure) Tj
T* (integration.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (6. BUILD AND EXECUTION WORKFLOW) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (BUILD) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (bash) Tj
T* (mkdir build) Tj
T* (cd build) Tj
T* (cmake ..) Tj
T* (make) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (EXAMPLE RUN) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (bash) Tj
T* (./happ simulate --cpu 4 --ram 8 --storage ssd --task rendering --complexity high --size 2) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (EXAMPLE COMPARE) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (bash) Tj
T* (./happ compare \\) Tj
T* (  --hw cpu=2,ram=4,storage=hdd,network=50,label=EdgeA \\) Tj
T* (  --hw cpu=8,ram=16,storage=nvme,network=500,label=EdgeB \\) Tj
T* (  --task database --complexity high --size 2) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (7. CURRENT STATUS VS ROADMAP) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Implemented:) Tj
T* (• Core CLI command handling) Tj
T* (• Analytical simulation engine) Tj
ET
